issue.title: Support exporting/importing experiments JSON through admin
issue.body:
It would be nice to be able to export an experiment to JSON from the admin on some instance (like prod), and then be able to load it into another instance (like local) to make it easier to reproduce prod issues locally.  Can either piggy back on `dumpdata` `loaddata` management commands, or maybe there's a library to do this.

┆Issue is synchronized with this [Jira Task](https://mozilla-hub.atlassian.net/browse/EXP-1867)

pull_request.title: fix #6639 feat(nimbus): add import/export to nimbus experiment admin page
pull_request.body:
Because

* it is helpful for development and testing to be able to copy experiments from prod to dev

This commit

* adds the ability to export selected experiments to a file
* adds the ability to import experiments from a file

Other Info
* "experiment" here refers to Nimbus Experiments
* Note that import will perform an update if the experiment identifier matches an existing experiment
* We are not concerned about exact matches for all nested objects, so in some cases using a dev user is acceptable

Export Context
* Admin page Action (available by selecting the desired experiments and selecting the export option in the dropdown)
* Should produce valid output in the selected format, including the experiment info + `changes` (list/array), `branches` (list/array), and `reference_branch_slug` (string)

Import Context
* Should be able to take the output file produced by Export and create/update an experiment, including change logs and branches
* Available via Nimbus Experiments admin page (button in upper right)
* Import button directs to import form with dropdown list of file type options
    * Select the file and type that you exported previously

Screenshot of additions to the Nimbus Experiment Admin page (see Action selection and Import button):
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/102263964/165592512-6cb26e43-997f-4555-af3d-72d3c29a3218.png)

comment.body:
➤ Benjamin Bangert commented:

Looks good, this will need Jon Buckley or Dustin Lactin to review/appprove.

review.body:
Fantastic!!  Everything looks broadly right to me, bunch of nitty code style rambling, but nothing significant.

I think the user association issue needs some attention though, if I do the following

```
make refresh up
<export experiment>
make refresh SKIP_DUMMY=1 up
<import experiment>
```

then the random factory user created in the first pass won't exist in the db in the second pass which is roughly analagous to some real user in prod not existing in local dev, and it fails with

```
Errors

    Line number: 1 - User matching query does not exist. 
```

so probably do need to either

1) get_or_create the Auth.User at import time
2) force override the user with one that will exist in local dev ie `dev@example.com`

to get around it.

But this is great, thank you @mikewilli for taking the time to dig into this this is gonna save so much hassle in the future 🙏 🙏 🙏 🙏

issue.title: Remove check for `null` from `onTextInput` in `CollectionManager`

labels.name: priority: p3
labels.description: This priority level reflects our backlog.

issue.body: It is not possible for `event.target.value` to be null, but we are checking for it at https://github.com/mozilla/addons-frontend/blob/master/src/amo/components/CollectionManager/index.js#L190. This check is unnecessary, and impossible to test now that we have moved to an integration test via the `Collection` page, so we should remove this check.
